# Fixture FM4b: Nested collections and single-element list blank nodes.
#
# Hypothesis: Implementations that flatten or confuse list nesting will
# produce wrong graphs. The outer list's rdf:first for `((1))` must be
# the blank node heading the inner list, not `1` itself.
#
# Expected for `(1)`:
#   _:b0 rdf:first "1"^^xsd:integer .
#   _:b0 rdf:rest  rdf:nil .
#   <http://example/s> <http://example/p> _:b0 .
#
# Expected for `((1))`:
#   outer: _:out rdf:first _:inn . _:out rdf:rest rdf:nil .
#   inner: _:inn rdf:first "1"^^xsd:integer . _:inn rdf:rest rdf:nil .
#
# Divergence signal: FactOnlyIn or ObjectMismatch on rdf:first / rdf:rest
# targets if nesting is flattened.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.8.

<http://example/s> <http://example/p1> (1) .
<http://example/s> <http://example/p2> ((1)) .
<http://example/s> <http://example/p3> (1 2) .
